These are Puzzles for 1x7 Level 8

.:: Puzzle 1x7-Level-8-1::.
There are 7 different favourite beverages: milk, juice, sprite, tea, cola, water, fanta
 1. the person drinking milk is somewhere to the right of the person drinking cola##5
 2. the person drinking tea is somewhere between the person drinking water and the person drinking cola##7
 3. the person drinking juice is somewhere between the person drinking water and the person drinking milk##7
 4. the person drinking juice is somewhere to the left of the person drinking sprite##5
 5. the person drinking fanta is not to the left of the person drinking water##8
 6. the person drinking juice is in an odd position##4
 7. the person drinking water is on the left or right of the person drinking tea##3
 8. the person drinking water is somewhere between the person drinking cola and the person drinking fanta##7
 9. the person drinking sprite is not to the right of the person drinking tea##8
10. the person drinking milk is on the left of the person drinking juice##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1       |     2     |    3     |      4      |  5   |  6  |   7    |
| Beverage   | cola | milk | juice | sprite | tea | water | fanta |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x7-Level-8-2::.
7 different games are played: domino, poker, chess, backgammon, bridge, mah-jongg, whist
 1. the person playing mah-jongg is the person playing mah-jongg##1
 2. the person playing chess is somewhere to the left of the person playing domino##5
 3. the person playing mah-jongg is somewhere to the right of the person playing poker##5
 4. the person playing poker is in an even position##4
 5. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left or right of the person playing whist##3
 6. the person playing backgammon is somewhere to the left of the person playing poker##5
 7. the person playing domino is on the left of the person playing bridge##1
 8. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left of the person playing whist##1
 9. the person playing whist is in an even position##4
10. the person playing bridge is not to the left of the person playing domino##8

.:: Answer ::.
|         |   1    |    2     |    3     |     4      |       5       |    6     |      7       |
| Game   | backgammon | poker | mah-jongg | whist | chess | domino | bridge |

